    <text>
        <body>
            <div xml:id="d.1">
                <head type="title">Tamás Szalaházy to Miklós Oláh (Bratislava, 2 January
                    1530)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p xml:id="reg.p.1"> 1. Constant troubles are hindering him in writing
                            letters: King John I is attacking Eger and everyone who has gathered
                            from Košice to Eger to defend this castle. 2. The wine has run out, and
                            he is asking that the Queen instruct the appropriate bodies to send good
                            quality wine, and a larger quantity than before. 3. Habardanecz has been
                            captured by King John I, while György Báthori and György Sulyok would
                            swear allegiance to King John I, supposedly only as a pretence.</p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb facs="15300102_1_1.jpg"/>
                <p xml:id="p.1">Idem Nicolao Olao.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.2">[1.] Noli te rogo in deteriorem accipere partem, quod raras ad te
                    litteras dare soleam: faciunt me assiduae curae et occupationes non quidem
                    immemorem officii, sed adeo anxium, ut non semper possim, quod maxime cuperem
                    amicis vel scribendo gratificari. <placeName>Agria</placeName><note
                        type="critic" xml:id="note.1">Eger.</note> iampridem vehementissime
                    periclitatur. <persName>Ioannes</persName>, quas potuit vires omnes Hungaricas,
                    Polonicas, infernas et superas in illius loci expugnationem, id est ad fideles
                        <persName>regis</persName>, qui a <placeName>Cassovia</placeName><note
                        type="critic" xml:id="note.2">Košice.</note> usque
                        <placeName>Agriam</placeName> in illius arcis defensionem convenerunt
                    debellandos. Exercitus <persName>regis</persName> dici vix potest, quam sit <add
                        corresp="Olahus" type="insert">timidus, dicere volebam</add> cautus, omnia
                    circumspicit, omnia etiam, quae fieri non possint, futura existimat. Sic fiet
                    nos etc. <persName>Maiestati reginali</persName> servitutem meam commendes,
                    rogo. </p>
                <p xml:id="p.3">[2.] Tricesimator duo vasa vini dedit tam exigua, ut utrumque
                    quinque, aut sex diebus sit exhaustum, negat se daturum plura,
                        <placeName>Posonii</placeName> deputat quibusdam in locis, unde vix iusto
                    vini pretio huc adveherentur. Cura, ut <persName>maiestas reginalis</persName>
                    mandet, reddantur <placeName>Posonii</placeName> et bona et non <del
                        corresp="Olahus">ade perma</del><add corresp="Olahus" type="corr">adeo
                        parva</add>. </p>
                <p xml:id="p.4">[3.] Ad maiestatem reginalem nihil est, quod scribere possim aliud,
                    quam quod audio <persName>Habardanecz</persName><note type="critic"
                        xml:id="note.3">János Habardanecz, see Ep.
                            5.<ref>/o:olahus.tei.15290111_1</ref></note> in
                        <persName>Ioannis</persName> captivitatem deductum. </p>
                <pb facs="15300102_1_2.jpg"/>
                <p xml:id="p.5"><persName>Georgius de Bathor</persName><note type="critic"
                        xml:id="note.4">Probably György I Báthori (†1531), he was Master of Stables
                            <hi rend="italic">(magister agazonum regalium)</hi> from 1505, and <hi
                            rend="italic">ispán</hi> of Szatmár, Zaránd, Zala, and Somogy counties,
                        for more see <hi rend="smallcap">C. Tóth</hi> 2009, 21–32.</note> et
                        <persName>episcopus Quinqueeclesiensis</persName><note type="critic"
                        xml:id="note.5">György II Sulyok (†1538) was Bishop of Pécs between
                        1526–1535 and 1537–1538.</note> ad <persName>Ioannem</persName> miserunt
                    oratores, impetrataque gratia se fideles fore promiserunt, ficte, ut nobis
                    significant. Sed talia figmenta non libenter audio, utinam non deteriora
                    audiamus. Sumus tardi, lenti, timidi. Vale. </p>
                <p xml:id="p.6"><placeName>Posonii</placeName> secundo Ianuarii 1530. </p>
            </div>
